    body: `GetSign creates unique URLs that let signers complete documents without email threads or logins. Links work best for single-signer scenarios and can be shared via email, WhatsApp, Slack, or SMS; sessions are encrypted with access logging, and signatures track in real time. Step 1 - Board setup: install GetSign, upload a template (PDF or DOCX), and create a Status column (e.g., Generate Link) and a URL/link column (e.g., Signing Link). Step 2 - Template prep: open GetSign in Item View and preview; if a signature field is missing, click Edit Template, drag the signature field, then Save and close. Step 3 - Manual generation: in Item View click Share, select Generate Link; the URL saves to the Signing Link column. Step 4 - Automated (optional): in Settings select the status column that triggers automation, set the trigger value (e.g., Done), and choose the column for storing the link, then save. Step 5 - Track status: view who signed, timestamps, and download from the File column. Limitation: each signing link supports only one signer per document; multiple signers require separate links.`,
