    body: `GetSign automates creation of shareable signing links for documents requiring multiple signatures. Step 1 - Prepare the template: in GetSign settings, open or create a template, assign distinct roles for each signer (e.g., Client Manager, Client Legal), map one role to a specific team member and another to an Email column, optionally assign form fields to signer roles, then save. Step 2 - Activate link generation: open GetSign app settings, scroll to Share and Track, and toggle it on. Step 3 - Select trigger column and value: choose a Status column to trigger generation, select a status value (e.g., Generate Link), and select or create a Link column. Step 4 - Configure email validation: in Share & Track, find the Email Validation toggle — Off for direct link access without verification, On to require signers assigned to an email column to enter a One-Time Password (OTP). Save. Step 5 - Trigger: create/update a board item, ensure email columns have correct addresses, and change the Status column to the trigger value. Best practices: test all roles and fields before deploying, keep email data accurate, enable OTP for sensitive documents, and inform signers they receive one link and must select their role on opening.`,
