    keywords: ["custom domain", "email", "getsign send", "dns records", "cname", "dkim", "custom mail from", "domain verification", "sender name", "deliverability", "propagation", "monday.com"],
    body: `Configure GetSign to send emails from your own domain. Step 1 - Add root domain: in GetSign Send, go to Domain Configuration in settings, enter your root domain (e.g., yourcompany.com), and select Begin Domain Verification. Step 2 - Add DNS records: GetSign provides CNAME records to copy into your DNS provider; these set up DKIM Authentication (secure delivery) and Custom Mail From (so emails display your domain). Add the records through your DNS provider (GoDaddy, Namecheap, cPanel, Cloudflare, Squarespace, Wix, Bluehost, AWS Route 53, Google Cloud DNS, DigitalOcean). DNS can take up to 24-48 hours to propagate, though often faster. Step 3 - Verify: return to GetSign, check the confirmation box, and click Verify; green checkmarks indicate success. Step 4 - Configure sender details: in GetSign Send, enter your sender name and email using the verified domain (e.g., hello@yourcompany.com), and optionally set email language. All subsequent emails then send from your custom domain, improving brand consistency and deliverability.`,
