    body: `Step 1 - Create a board: set up columns for tenant name, property owner name, email addresses, property type, lease dates, and status tracking (sent, viewed, signed, failed). Step 2 - Upload and configure template: install GetSign and upload your rental agreement; configure signature fields by dragging tenant and landlord signature areas, mapping each to the corresponding email columns. Step 3 - Configure signature settings: enable e-signature collection and map signer roles (Tenant to Tenant Email, Landlord to Property Owner Email); select your status column for tracking. If multiple signers are required, GetSign enforces the signing sequence. Step 4 - Automate sending: use GetSign Send (Email Delivery) to set a trigger status such as "Send for Signature"; customize sender name, subject, message. When status updates, GetSign automatically emails both parties with secure signing links. Step 5 - Track signed agreements: set a trigger status such as "Signed" and map the signature link column to save URLs; signed PDFs store directly in the item. Step 6 - Bulk send: select multiple rows and update status to "Send for Signature"; filter by "Not Signed" to view pending agreements.`,
