    keywords: ["digital signature", "cryptographic certificate", "tamper detection", "audit log", "timestamp", "pdf certificate", "eidas", "esign act", "ueta", "hipaa", "external signers", "docx template", "plan availability", "getsign"],
    body: `GetSign uses cryptographic certificates to bind signatures to signer identity and document content; each signer's action is paired with an embedded certificate proving identity and intent. Secure signatures are generated automatically when documents are sent through monday.com, with no manual setup. Security architecture: (1) Encryption and certification — signatures include embedded digital certificates linking signers to their actions; (2) Tamper detection — any change to a signed document invalidates the digital certificate; (3) Audit logging — each signing action gets timestamp tracking and a complete audit trail. Technical capabilities: signed outputs are PDFs with embedded certificates and verification metadata; DOCX files are accepted as templates for generation; external signers do not need a GetSign or monday.com account and their sessions are tracked separately; signed PDFs open in standard readers to display certificate verification. Compliance cited: eIDAS AES (EU Regulation 910/2014), ESIGN Act (US), UETA (US state-level), and HIPAA. Plan availability: digital signature functionality is included in the Standard, Pro, and Enterprise plans only; Basic plan users must upgrade.`,
